Your project uses **MSTest v2 (2.2.10)**. Here are the breaking changes that affect your code when upgrading to v3:

### 1. Package references → replace with `MSTest` metapackage
```xml
<!-- Remove MSTest.TestFramework, MSTest.TestAdapter, and replace with: -->
<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="3.8.0" />
```

### 2. `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` overload removed (line 13)
```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual);
// After
Assert.AreEqual<object>(expected, actual);
```

### 3. `Assert.AreSame(object, object)` overload removed (line 20)
```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreSame(obj, obj);
// After
Assert.AreSame<object>(obj, obj);
```

### 4. `DataRow` strict type matching (lines 24–25)
`1L` (long) doesn't match parameter type `int`. Fix the literals:
```csharp
// Before
[DataRow(1L, "Alice")]
[DataRow(2L, "Bob")]
public void GetUserName_ReturnsCorrectName(int id, string expectedName)

// After
[DataRow(1, "Alice")]
[DataRow(2, "Bob")]
public void GetUserName_ReturnsCorrectName(int id, string expectedName)
```

### 5. `[Timeout]` behavior unified
Your `[Timeout(3000)]` on line 32 will still work, but timeout behavior is now consistent across .NET Core and Framework. Verify the value is still appropriate.

